Quick Pass Through the Easy Ones (#6)

Not sure if you wanted the all to come in one at a time, but this quick
pass adds nearly all the missing `eth_*` methods that don't require new
types.

I moved `GetBlockTransactionCountByHash` down one to preserve
alphabetical ordering.

Add eth_getTransactionReceipt (#4)

Introducing method to getTransactionReceipt documented as is here:
https://ethereum.github.io/execution-apis/api-documentation/#eth_gettransactionreceipt

Note that this is based on main but depends a branch that has not yet
been merged (so it looks weird and isn't passing CI). Once the other one
hits main I will rebase.

Fix ERC -> EIP Naming

I mistakenly assumed that ERC was an EIP that was final. This is not
the case. ERCs are for proposing standards related to the Ethereum
ecosystem (such as smart contract standards) while EIPs are changes to
the Ethereum protocol. These transactions types are all changes to the
protocol and are therefore EIPs.

Thanks @bh2smith for raising this!

add getBlockReceipts (#3)

1. Creating new type `TransactionReceipt` along with enums:
   - `TransactionReceiptKind` (for the transaction "type" field).
   - `TransactionReceiptStatus` (for success vs failed transactions)
2. Add ethrpc method `eth_getBlockRecipts` according to the spec defined
here is as in
https://ethereum.github.io/execution-apis/api-documentation/#eth_getblockreceipts

Fix Build And Update To Production Safe SDK and API (#1)

Currently running `make host` on a clean checkout doesn't work. 

The reason being that `index.html` is copied in the beginning of the makefile (at `npm run bundle`) and therefore the `index.html` target (that does the crucial replacements of style and js code) believes it has nothing more to do since `dist/index.html` already exists at this point. This leads to the Safe App loading with a blank screen (as no logic is injected).

Additionally, this PR modifies the app to use the latest SDK version and point to the production Safe transaction services (it used to point to the EIP-1271 preview services while they were under development).
